## State Configuration

### State Properties

Each state within a model has:

{% table %}
- Property
- Description
---
- **Name**
- State identifier (max 255 characters)
---
- **Color**
- Visual color from preset palette or custom hex
---
- **Position**
- Display order (affects dropdown and visualization)
---
- **Is Initial**
- Marks the starting state (only one per model)
---
- **Is Terminal**
- Marks an end state (sale workflow complete)
{% /table %}

### Commission Properties

{% table %}
- Property
- Description
---
- **Triggers Commission**
- Commission is calculated when entering this state
---
- **Reclaims Commission**
- Previously earned commission is reversed when entering this state
{% /table %}

### Address Properties

{% table %}
- Property
- Description
---
- **Cancels Address**
- Marks the address as inactive when entering this state
---
- **Active Address**
- Marks the address as active when entering this state
{% /table %}

### Managing States

**Add a State:**

1. In the edit dialog, go to the States tab
1. Click **Add State**
1. Configure the state properties
1. Save

**Edit a State:**

1. Click on the state in the list
1. Modify properties
1. Save

**Remove a State:**

- Click the remove button on the state row
- Cannot remove if sales reference this state

> **Note:** Each model must have at least one state and exactly one initial state.

## Transitions

### What are Transitions?

Transitions define which state changes are allowed. For example:

- Proposal → Confirmed (allowed)
- Proposal → Cancelled (allowed)
- Cancelled → Proposal (not allowed)

### Configuring Transitions

1. In the edit dialog, go to the Transitions tab
1. For each transition, specify:
   - **From State** - Starting state
   - **To State** - Destination state
   - **Is Default** - Makes this the default transition option
   - **Auto-Transition Days** (optional) - Automatically transition after N days

### Auto-Transitions

Set a number of days after which a sale automatically moves to the next state. Useful for:

- Auto-confirming proposals after a waiting period
- Auto-cancelling stale proposals

## Editing Models

### Edit Model Info

1. Click the actions menu on a model
1. Select **Edit**
1. Go to the Info tab
1. Update name, description, or set as default
1. Save

### Edit States and Transitions

1. Open the Edit dialog
1. Use the tabs to switch between:
   - **Info** - Model name and description
   - **States** - Manage state properties
   - **Transitions** - Manage allowed transitions

## Visualizing Models

### Flow Diagram

View an interactive diagram of your model:

1. Click the actions menu on a model
1. Select **Visualize**
1. See the state flow diagram

The diagram shows:

- State nodes with colors
- State properties (Initial, Terminal, Commission flags)
- Arrows showing transitions
- Auto-transition days labeled on edges
- Drag to reposition, scroll to zoom
- Mini-map for navigation

## Project Assignments

### Assign to Projects

1. Click the actions menu on a model
1. Select **Assign to Projects**
1. Toggle projects on/off
1. Changes save automatically

> **Note:** Each project can only have one sale model assigned. Assigning a new model replaces the existing assignment.

> **Note:** Archived models cannot be assigned to projects.

## Setting Default Model

One model can be marked as the default:

1. Edit the model
1. Enable the **Default** checkbox
1. Save

The default model is automatically suggested when creating sales. Only one model per team can be default.

## Archiving Models

### Archive a Model

1. Click the actions menu on a model
1. Select **Archive**
1. Confirm

When archived:

- Model is unassigned from all projects
- Cannot be used for new sales
- Existing sales using the model's states are preserved
- Can be restored later

> **Note:** Models with active sales referencing their states can be archived but not deleted.

### Restore a Model

1. Enable **Show archived**
1. Click the actions menu on the archived model
1. Select **Unarchive**

After restoring, reassign the model to projects as needed.

## Deleting Models

Models can only be permanently deleted if no sales reference their states:

1. Archive the model first
1. If no sales use it, the **Delete** option appears
1. Confirm permanent deletion

## Audit History

Team owners can view change history:

1. Click the actions menu on a model
1. Select **View Audit History**
1. See changes to the model, its states, and transitions

